      "content": "It's a very common feeling, as the initial years are heavily weighted toward interest, which can feel frustrating. Many homeowners cope by focusing on the long-term goal rather than the monthly breakdown, reminding themselves that they are building equity over time. Alternatively, some people make extra principal payments when they can afford it, which drastically accelerates the payoff and reduces total interest paid. This proactive approach helps combat that feeling of stagnation.",
      "source": "target",
